A wrapper for a function that can be run by an overseer.

  • Constructor Details

    • Arc

      public Arc(boolean safe)
      A safe arc is one that cannot be set to a status that is less than its current status. This means it can only be run once. This is useful for preventing deadlocks and livelocks, as even though arcs cannot directly ticktock an overseer, it can easily do so indirectly by leveraging nodes and safe arcs.
      Parameters:
      safe - true if this arc is safe

    • Arc

      public Arc(String name, boolean safe)
      A safe arc is one that cannot be set to a status that is less than its current status. This means it can only be run once. This is useful for preventing deadlocks and livelocks, as even though arcs cannot directly ticktock an overseer, it can easily do so indirectly by leveraging nodes and safe arcs.
      Parameters:
      name - the name of this arc
      safe - true if this arc is safe

    • returnDatum

      protected void returnDatum(String datumName, Object datum)
      Returns the datum with the given name to the overseer's cache by calling Node.addDatum(String, Object). The datum can be null.
      Parameters:
      datumName - the name of the datum
      datum - the datum to return
      Throws:
      NullPointerException - if the datum name is not associated with any node
      IllegalArgumentException - if the node with this datum is not an output of this arc

    • alias

      protected void alias(String name, String alias)
      Define an alias for an Input or Output's name (Input.name(), Output.name()). Use this when the name of your datum is dynamic. The Input/Output name still has to be unique and may be left empty and autogenerated from the field name. For example, 
       
 new AutoArc() {
 @Input
  String inputStr;

  {
        // some function declared outside of this class
        alias("inputStr", getDynamicInputName());
  }

 @Override
  void run() {
        System.out.println(inputStr); // would print getDatum(getDynamicInputName())
  }
 }
      Parameters:
      name - the name of the Input or Output
      alias - the alias to use
      See Also:
      • Input
      • Output
      • getDatum(String)

    • getStatus

      public ArcStatus getStatus()

    • setStatus

      protected void setStatus(ArcStatus status)
      Sets the status of the arc. The status cannot be set to null. The status cannot be changed if the arc is already finished. If the arc is safe, the status cannot be set to a status that is less (see ArcStatus.stage()) than the current status.
      Parameters:
      status - the new status of the arc
      Throws:
      NullPointerException - if the status is null
      IllegalStateException - if the arc is already finished
      IllegalArgumentException - if the arc is safe and the status is less than the current status
